This paper discusses the behavior and performance of open proxies, which are commonly used for circumventing censorship and region restrictions. As such, it is likely to fall under the categories of computer security (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
